to ask me out for dinner.

307
00:39:51,860 --> 00:39:56,490
No. I don't date students.

308
00:40:06,330 --> 00:40:12,420
I can see it's dangerous for you.
But if the government trusts me ...

309
00:40:12,670 --> 00:40:16,510
... maybe you could.

310
00:40:21,300 --> 00:40:25,720
It takes a lot more than just fancy flying.

311
00:40:38,150 --> 00:40:42,410
Crash and burn, huh, Mav?.

312
00:40:44,330 --> 00:40:46,830
Slider ...

313
00:40:48,580 --> 00:40:51,670
You stink.

314
00:41:00,470 --> 00:41:02,430
Let's go!

315
00:42:22,670 --> 00:42:26,930
Come on, Mav. Just one more game.
That evens it up.

316
00:42:27,180 --> 00:42:31,560
- I got some things to take care of.
- Just one more game.

317
00:42:31,810 --> 00:42:36,230
Please? For me?
Come on ... For me?

318
00:43:10,720 --> 00:43:14,020
Damn it.

319
00:43:24,440 --> 00:43:27,320
Lieutenant?

320
00:43:31,780 --> 00:43:36,580
- What? No singing?
- Look, I'm ...

321
00:43:36,870 --> 00:43:40,540
No apologies.

322
00:43:46,420 --> 00:43:51,640
If you don't mind, I'll just take a quick
shower while you're finishing up here.

323
00:43:53,930 --> 00:43:58,350
I do mind. I'm hungry.

324
00:44:01,520 --> 00:44:05,190
And then I thought about it.

325
00:44:05,440 --> 00:44:09,910
I thought,
"You know, he's a smart guy."

326
00:44:10,160 --> 00:44:16,080
"Why don't you just tell him
why you've got him here?"

327
00:44:17,960 --> 00:44:21,330
It's the MiG.

328
00:44:23,630 --> 00:44:30,340
The MiG. You're the only pilot
who's been up against a MiG-28.

329
00:44:31,760 --> 00:44:37,270
I'm trying for this big promotion.
If I get it, I won't be here much longer.

330
00:44:37,520 --> 00:44:41,480
Seems to me you've got it all figured out.

331
00:44:43,360 --> 00:44:48,490
Except you did forget the wine.

332
00:44:48,740 --> 00:44:51,030
Sorry.

333
00:44:51,280 --> 00:44:56,660
- You always get what you want?
- No, not always. Yeah, maybe.

334
00:44:56,910 --> 00:45:01,370
Then relax about the MiG.

335
00:45:14,470 --> 00:45:18,220
This music ...

336
00:45:18,470 --> 00:45:21,850
An old friend?

337
00:45:22,100 --> 00:45:28,030
My folks loved it.
I haven't heard this in years.

338
00:45:28,280 --> 00:45:33,320
My mother used to call from her room
and have me play this over and over.

339
00:45:33,570 --> 00:45:37,990
I got so sick of it.

340
00:45:38,240 --> 00:45:44,750
But not her. She'd sit up there alone,
just listening for hours.

341
00:45:45,000 --> 00:45:51,510
Just listening.
She died shortly after him.

342
00:45:51,760 --> 00:45:56,220
What happened to your father?.

343
00:45:59,770 --> 00:46:06,440
I figured with your security clearance
you'd know more about it than I do.

344
00:46:06,690 --> 00:46:12,030
Well, I didn't get that far.

345
00:46:12,240 --> 00:46:15,490
It's a big mystery.

346
00:46:15,740 --> 00:46:20,450
He disappeared in an F-4,
November 5th, 1965.

347
00:46:23,040 --> 00:46:28,290
The stink of it was ... he screwed up.

348
00:46:28,540 --> 00:46:33,920
No way.
My old man was a great fighter pilot.

349
00:46:36,800 --> 00:46:42,560
But who the hell knows?
It's all classified.

350
00:46:42,810 --> 00:46:47,310
- Somebody must know.
- Yeah, somebody knows everything.

351
00:46:47,560 --> 00:46:52,650
Is that why
you're always second best up there?

352
00:46:52,900 --> 00:46:57,200
You are direct, aren't you.

353
00:47:03,450 --> 00:47:07,500
I'm sorry I was late.

354
00:47:07,750 --> 00:47:13,710
- I'm sorry for being direct.
- No apologies.

355
00:47:13,960 --> 00:47:19,390
This is going to be complicated.

356
00:47:29,060 --> 00:47:33,360
- Where are you going?
- I'm gonna take a shower.

357
00:47:37,780 --> 00:47:42,790
Thank you. I enjoyed being here.

358
00:48:19,860 --> 00:48:24,740
It looks like you need another shower.

359
00:48:24,990 --> 00:48:28,410
Right.

360
00:48:32,420 --> 00:48:35,800
I'm gonna be honest with you.

361
00:48:36,050 --> 00:48:41,140
Your MiG sighting
is really important to my work, but ...

362
00:48:45,180 --> 00:48:50,270
I don't normally invite students
to my house. You're ...

363
00:48:58,530 --> 00:49:02,070
But please understand,
I still have a job to do.

364
00:49:28,180 --> 00:49:33,650
I'm glad we got that straight.

365
00:49:49,120 --> 00:49:54,000
I told her how tough it is here.
My ass dragging like an old tired dog.

366
00:49:54,250 --> 00:49:57,550
I told her you didn't even have a woman.

367
00:49:57,800 --> 00:50:01,510
She said, "He probably
doesn't have one, but eight."

368
00:50:06,510 --> 00:50:12,060
- Hi!
- Daddy.

369
00:50:17,610 --> 00:50:23,570
Goose tells me you're in love
with one of your instructors.

370
00:50:23,820 --> 00:50:28,910
I didn't tell her that. I can't believe
you said that. That was a secret.

371
00:50:36,580 --> 00:50:41,960
The bogey has good position right here.
Freeze frame. A moment of choice.

372
00:50:42,210 --> 00:50:46,510
The F-14 is defensive.
He has a chance to bug out right here.

373
00:50:46,760 --> 00:50:53,230
Better to retire and save your aircraft
than push a bad position.

374
00:50:53,480 --> 00:50:58,690
Charlie, jump in here any time. You stay
in that diamond another three seconds, -

375
00:50:58,940 --> 00:51:03,740
- the bogey's gonna blow you away.
You take a hard right, select zone five ...

376
00:51:03,990 --> 00:51:08,910
You can extend an escape.
You made a bad choice.

377
00:51:09,160 --> 00:51:16,330
- Charlie?
- Aircraft one performs a split S?

378
00:51:16,580 --> 00:51:20,750
That's the last thing you should do.
The MiG's right on your tail.

379
00:51:21,000 --> 00:51:27,590
Freeze there. The MiG has you in
his gunsight. What were you thinking?

380
00:51:27,840 --> 00:51:32,350
You don't have time to think up there.
If you think, you're dead.

381
00:51:32,600 --> 00:51:38,350
That's a big gamble
with a $30 million plane.

382
00:51:43,650 --> 00:51:48,860
Unfortunately, it worked.
The MiG never got a clean shot.

383
00:51:49,110 --> 00:51:55,700
Maverick makes an aggressive vertical
move and defeats him with a missile.

384
00:51:55,960 --> 00:52:01,340
The encounter was a victory, but we
show it as an example of what not to do.

385
00:52:03,340 --> 00:52:05,630
Next.

386
00:52:05,880 --> 00:52:09,340
Gutsiest move I ever saw, man.

387
00:52:11,890 --> 00:52:17,140
Now then, this is a perfect example
of a textbook manoeuvre.

388
00:52:29,240 --> 00:52:30,950
Lieutenant?

389
00:52:43,840 --> 00:52:48,800
My review of your performance was
right on, in my professional opinion.

390
00:52:49,050 --> 00:52:52,850
I can't hear you.

391
00:53:11,280 --> 00:53:17,620
Jesus! And you call me reckless? When
I fly, my crew and my plane come first.

392
00:53:17,870 --> 00:53:24,250
I'm gonna finish my sentence. My review
of your performance was right on.

393
00:53:24,500 --> 00:53:30,130
I see some real genius in your flying,
but I can't say that in there.

394
00:53:30,380 --> 00:53:34,220
I was afraid they'd see right through me.

395
00:53:34,470 --> 00:53:39,980
I don't want anyone to know
that I've fallen for you.

396
00:55:25,040 --> 00:55:28,630
- Hey, Maverick?. Hear about lce?
- What's that?

397
00:55:28,880 --> 00:55:33,010
- He won another one.
