Go fetch him.
Doesn't he ever embarrass you?

444
01:01:44,750 --> 01:01:50,750
- Hell no. Well, there was the time ...
- Admiral's daughter.

445
01:01:51,000 --> 01:01:56,260
He told me all about the time
you went ballistic with Penny Benjamin.

446
01:01:56,510 --> 01:01:59,010
Did he? Great.

447
01:01:59,260 --> 01:02:04,740
He tells me about all of them. My angel
Goose goes home early for church.

448
01:02:04,990 --> 01:02:09,280
- You go home with the hot women.
- Thank you, Carole.

449
01:02:09,530 --> 01:02:14,870
I'm gonna go embarrass myself
with Goose for a while.

450
01:02:31,180 --> 01:02:36,140
I'd love to be able to warn you off about
Maverick, but I just love him to death.

451
01:02:37,640 --> 01:02:42,650
I've known Pete for a lot of years.
One thing's for certain.

452
01:02:42,900 --> 01:02:47,990
There are hearts breaking wide open
all over the world tonight.

453
01:02:48,240 --> 01:02:52,620
Unless you are a fool,
that boy is off the market.

454
01:02:52,870 --> 01:02:58,210
He is 100%%% prime time in love with you.

455
01:02:58,460 --> 01:03:04,090
Hey, Goose, you big stud.
Take me to bed or lose me forever.

456
01:03:04,340 --> 01:03:07,970
Show me the way home, honey.

457
01:03:08,220 --> 01:03:11,340
Come on, brother, sing with the family.

458
01:03:42,840 --> 01:03:47,670
Maverick, you big stud ...

459
01:03:47,920 --> 01:03:52,270
Take me to bed or lose me forever.

460
01:04:04,530 --> 01:04:07,950
This is hop 31.
Two weeks to graduation.

461
01:04:08,200 --> 01:04:11,540
The Top Gun trophy
is still up forgrabs.

462
01:04:55,000 --> 01:04:58,590
The score is tied. Time for the big one.

463
01:04:58,840 --> 01:05:04,930
- Are you up for this one, Maverick?.
- Just a walk in the park.

464
01:05:06,840 --> 01:05:11,520
Contact. Multiple bogeys. Two miles.
Looks like they're going away from us.

465
01:05:11,770 --> 01:05:15,690
- I see them. Right, two o'clock. I'm in.
- I'm in.

466
01:05:35,830 --> 01:05:39,460
That son of a bitch cut me off.

467
01:05:46,340 --> 01:05:52,230
Come on. Jesus Christ, lce.
Take the shot. Get the hell out of there.

468
01:05:52,480 --> 01:05:56,240
I can't get the angle. I'm too close.
I'm switching to guns.

469
01:05:56,480 --> 01:05:59,620
Fire or clear!

470
01:06:04,250 --> 01:06:10,250
- Christ, I can take a shot right here.
- 20 seconds and I've got him.

471
01:06:16,220 --> 01:06:20,300
- I'm moving in. I've got the shot.
- Come on, Mav.

472
01:06:22,060 --> 01:06:25,640
- He's getting impatient. Take the shot.
- 10 more seconds.

473
01:06:27,810 --> 01:06:32,480
Get the hell out of there.
Come off my right. I'm in.

474
01:06:32,730 --> 01:06:35,650
- Five more seconds.
- I'm in.

475
01:06:35,900 --> 01:06:38,030
I'm off. Shit.

476
01:06:40,660 --> 01:06:43,330
We're in a jetwash. Shit!

477
01:06:46,500 --> 01:06:52,290
This is not good. We've got a flame-out.
Engine one is out ... Engine two is out.

478
01:06:52,540 --> 01:06:55,550
I'm losing control. I can't control it!

479
01:06:59,800 --> 01:07:03,600
It's coupling up. This is not good!

480
01:07:03,850 --> 01:07:09,270
Mayday, mayday. Mav's in trouble.
He's in a flat spin heading out to sea!

481
01:07:11,190 --> 01:07:14,730
Altitude 8,000 ... 7,000 ...

482
01:07:14,980 --> 01:07:17,780
We're at 6,000!

483
01:07:19,530 --> 01:07:22,420
I can't reach the ejection handle!

484
01:07:24,590 --> 01:07:31,210
- You're gonna have to punch us out.
- I can't reach the ejection handle!

485
01:07:31,460 --> 01:07:34,970
- Eject ...
- Watch the canopy!

486
01:07:51,570 --> 01:07:53,990
Goose ... Oh, no!

487
01:07:57,660 --> 01:08:00,330
Oh, God.

488
01:08:47,710 --> 01:08:51,210
Sir, let go of him.
You've got to let him go, sir.

489
01:09:34,680 --> 01:09:40,480
- How are you doing?
- I'm all right.

490
01:09:40,730 --> 01:09:44,780
- Goose is dead.
- I know.

491
01:09:47,910 --> 01:09:52,370
You flyjets long enough,
something like this happens.

492
01:09:52,620 --> 01:09:56,960
He was my RIO, my responsibility.

493
01:09:59,040 --> 01:10:05,010
In my squadron in Vietnam,
we lost 8 of 18 aircraft. 10 men.

494
01:10:05,260 --> 01:10:11,510
The first one dies, you die too.
But there will be others.

495
01:10:11,760 --> 01:10:15,270
You can count on it.

496
01:10:15,520 --> 01:10:19,270
You've got to let him go.

497
01:10:20,480 --> 01:10:24,190
You've got to let him go.

498
01:10:40,290 --> 01:10:44,340
I think maybe it was my fault.

499
01:10:44,590 --> 01:10:47,920
I don't know.

500
01:10:48,170 --> 01:10:52,140
I don't know what the hell went wrong.

501
01:10:52,390 --> 01:10:57,350
I'd like to help. I know it's difficult.

502
01:11:02,940 --> 01:11:07,070
God, I want him back.

503
01:11:11,290 --> 01:11:15,800
I'll be here if you need me, okay?.

504
01:13:07,210 --> 01:13:11,120
God, he loved flying with you, Maverick.

505
01:13:28,310 --> 01:13:33,780
He would have flown anyway ...
without you.

506
01:13:34,030 --> 01:13:39,570
He'd have hated it,
but he would have done it.

507
01:13:58,760 --> 01:14:05,180
The spin was induced by the disruption
of air flow into the starboard engine.

508
01:14:05,430 --> 01:14:09,350
This disruption stalled the engine, -

509
01:14:09,600 --> 01:14:14,030
- which produced enough yaw rate
to induce a spin -

510
01:14:14,280 --> 01:14:17,650
- which was unrecoverable.

511
01:14:17,900 --> 01:14:23,450
There was no way Lieutenant Mitchell
could see or avoid the jetwash.

512
01:14:23,700 --> 01:14:28,920
The Board of lnquiry finds that he was
not at fault in the accident of 29 July.

513
01:14:29,170 --> 01:14:35,710
His record will be cleared. He's restored
to flight status without further delay.

514
01:14:36,880 --> 01:14:40,340
These proceedings are closed.

515
01:14:47,860 --> 01:14:51,450
Get him up flying, soon.

516
01:15:17,020 --> 01:15:22,770
- Come on, kid. Get in there. Engage.
- You've got a bogey at two o'clock.

517
01:15:27,320 --> 01:15:30,860
Take the shot, kid.

518
01:15:31,110 --> 01:15:34,570
You can engage any time, Maverick.

519
01:15:43,120 --> 01:15:47,800
- Where the hell are you going?
- It doesn't look good.

520
01:15:48,050 --> 01:15:53,380
What do you mean? It doesn't get
to look any better than that.

521
01:16:03,980 --> 01:16:08,020
Hey, man. We could have had him ...

522
01:16:10,230 --> 01:16:15,870
I'll fire when I'm goddamn
good and ready. You got that?

523
01:16:33,720 --> 01:16:38,980
- He won't engage.
- It's only been a few days.

524
01:16:39,230 --> 01:16:45,360
- He just might not make it back.
- Keep sending him up.

525
01:17:05,930 --> 01:17:08,590
Mitchell?

526
01:17:08,800 --> 01:17:13,220
I'm sorry about Goose.

527
01:17:14,600 --> 01:17:18,060
Everybody liked him.

528
01:17:22,070 --> 01:17:25,400
I'm sorry.

529
01:17:43,130 --> 01:17:47,050
Hi, it's Wolfman.

530
01:17:47,300 --> 01:17:49,220
Maverickjust quit.

531
01:18:12,780 --> 01:18:15,870
Excuse me ...

532
01:18:17,120 --> 01:18:20,120
- May l?
- Please.

533
01:18:29,060 --> 01:18:34,480
I'll have what he's having.
Hemlock, is it?

534
01:18:34,720 --> 01:18:39,310
Ice water.

535
01:18:41,070 --> 01:18:45,120
You weren't gonna say goodbye?

536
01:18:45,370 --> 01:18:50,150
I heard you got that job in Washington.
Congratulations.

537
01:18:50,410 --> 01:18:57,050
Thanks. But I wasn't gonna leave
without saying goodbye.

538
01:19:01,010 --> 01:19:05,510
- It's good to see you.
- Thanks.

539
01:19:07,180 --> 01:19:13,520
Where are you going?
You don't even have a ticket, do you?

540
01:19:13,770 --> 01:19:20,700
I've seen all the evidence, and it's not
your responsibility. It's not your fault.

541
01:19:21,860 --> 01:19:25,620
You're one of the best pilots in the Navy.

542
01:19:25,870 --> 01:19:30,290
What you do up there ... It's dangerous.

543
01:19:30,540 --> 01:19:35,540
- But you've got to go on.
- You don't understand.

544
01:19:36,670 --> 01:19:42,050
When I first met you,
you were larger than life.

545
01:19:43,970 --> 01:19:46,890
Look at you.

546
01:19:47,140 --> 01:19:52,310
You're not gonna be happy unless you're
going Mach 2 with your hair on fire.

547
01:19:52,560 --> 01:19:55,310
No, that's over. It's just over.

548
01:19:55,560 --> 01:20:01,820
To be the best of the best means you
make mistakes and then you go on.

549
01:20:02,070 --> 01:20:05,820
You don't think I know that?

550
01:20:06,070 --> 01:20:09,330
I'm here to help.

551
01:20:09,580 --> 01:20:17,470
Look, thank you. If I'd wanted help,
I would have asked for it.

552
01:20:23,720 --> 01:20:27,360
So, I'm too late.

553
01:20:27,610 --> 01:20:31,190
You've already left.

554
01:20:31,440 --> 01:20:38,410
You didn't learn a damn thing, did you?
Except to quit.

555
01:20:39,980 --> 01:20:44,960
You've got that manoeuvre down
real well.

556
01:20:50,500 --> 01:20:53,880
So long, Pete Mitchell.

557
01:21:18,530 --> 01:21:24,660
Hi, Maverick, come on in. How are you?
Sure you're feeling okay?.

558
01:21:24,910 --> 01:21:29,380
- Great.
- Jamie, come on. Can I get you a drink?.

559
01:21:29,630 --> 01:21:34,630
Make yourself comfortable.
Mike will be right down.

560
01:21:54,030 --> 01:21:59,950
I flew with your old man.
VF-51 , the Oriskany.

561
01:22:01,370 --> 01:22:07,880
You're a lot like he was.
Only better ... and worse.

562
01:22:09,920 --> 01:22:13,930
He was a natural heroic son of a bitch.

563
01:22:17,510 --> 01:22:21,440
So he did do it right.

564
01:22:23,560 --> 01:22:27,690
Yeah, he did it right.

565
01:22:35,700 --> 01:22:40,790
Is that why you fly the way you do?
Trying to prove something?

566
01:22:42,250 --> 01:22:45,960
Yeah, your old man did it right.

567
01:22:46,210 --> 01:22:50,340
What I'm about to tell you is classified.
It could end my career.

568
01:22:50,590 --> 01:22:53,760
We were in the worst dogfight ever.

569
01:22:54,010 --> 01:23:00,020
Bogeys like fireflies all over the sky.
His F-4 was hit, -

570
01:23:00,270 --> 01:23:03,230
- he was wounded, but he stayed.

571
01:23:03,480 --> 01:23:10,110
- Saved three planes before he bought it.
- How come I never heard that before?

572
01:23:10,360 --> 01:23:17,370
The battle occurred
over the wrong line on some map.

573
01:23:17,620 --> 01:23:21,250
- So you were there?
- I was there.

574
01:23:21,500 --> 01:23:27,800
- What's on your mind?
- My options, sir.

575
01:23:28,050 --> 01:23:32,550
Simple.
You've acquired enough points -

576
01:23:32,800 --> 01:23:37,810
- to show up tomorrow and graduate
with your class. Or you could quit.

577
01:23:40,020 --> 01:23:44,230
There'll be no disgrace.
That spin was hell.

578
01:23:44,480 --> 01:23:49,150
- So you think I should quit?
- I didn't say that.

579
01:23:49,400 --> 01:23:54,490
You feel responsible for Goose.
And you have a confidence problem.

580
01:23:56,410 --> 01:23:59,580
I won't blow sunshine up your ass.

581
01:23:59,840 --> 01:24:04,300
A good pilot is compelled
to evaluate what's happened -

582
01:24:04,550 --> 01:24:12,230
- and apply what he's learned. Up there,
we've got to push it. That's ourjob.

583
01:24:15,180 --> 01:24:19,650
It's your option, Lieutenant.
All yours.

584
01:24:30,910 --> 01:24:34,620
Sorry to bother you on a Sunday, sir.
Thank you for your time.

585
01:24:34,870 --> 01:24:38,750
No problem. Good luck.

586
01:25:26,800 --> 01:25:31,220
- Gentlemen ...
- Where's Maverick?.

587
01:25:31,470 --> 01:25:37,100
- I don't know where he is.
- You know what he's planning to do?

588
01:25:38,270 --> 01:25:42,940
It's got to be hard on the guy though.

589
01:26:12,230 --> 01:26:15,270
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

590
01:26:16,730 --> 01:26:20,450
- Congratulations.
- Thanks, Mav.

591
01:26:23,030 --> 01:26:29,120
Gentlemen, I hate to break up the party
before it gets out of hand ...

592
01:26:29,370 --> 01:26:34,460
Some of you have to depart
immediately. We have a crisis situation.

593
01:26:34,710 --> 01:26:38,510
Ice, Slider ...
Hollywood, Wolfman.

594
01:26:40,840 --> 01:26:45,850
- Maverick.
- Sir.

595
01:26:47,270 --> 01:26:52,770
Maverick, you'll get your RIO
when you get to the ship. If you don't ...

596
01:26:53,020 --> 01:26:57,280
... give me a call. I'll fly with you.

597
01:27:11,080 --> 01:27:16,670
The SS Layton has become disabled
and has wandered into foreign territory.

598
01:27:16,920 --> 01:27:22,680
A rescue operation will soon begin.
Your mission is to give it air support.

599
01:27:22,930 --> 01:27:29,720
There are MiGs in the area. If you
witness a hostile act, return fire.

600
01:27:30,890 --> 01:27:36,280
They carry the Exocet anti-ship missile.
They can fire it from 100 miles away.

601
01:27:36,520 --> 01:27:42,740
This is the real thing.
This is what you've been trained for.

602
01:27:43,000 --> 01:27:48,040
Make us proud.
Ice ... Hollywood, sector two.

603
01:27:48,280 --> 01:27:52,340
Maverick, you back them up with Merlin
on ready five.

604
01:27:52,590 --> 01:27:55,890
- Yes, sir.
- Rise.

605
01:27:57,930 --> 01:28:00,880
Excuse me, sir. This is not personal.

606
01:28:01,140 --> 01:28:07,190
- But is Maverick the best pilot to ..?
- I know what's on your mind. Get on it.

607
01:29:26,180 --> 01:29:29,570
You've got a pair of bogeys,
12 o'clock, 15 miles.

608
01:29:29,820 --> 01:29:35,540
Voodoo One, 090, radar contact
15 miles. They're doing 500 knots.

609
01:29:35,780 --> 01:29:38,450
Roger, that's your bogey.

610
01:29:40,570 --> 01:29:43,290
Dead ahead, 15 miles, 600 knots.

611
01:29:52,250 --> 01:29:56,220
They're at 15,000 feetnow, 10 miles.

612
01:29:56,470 --> 01:30:00,690
800 knots. Dead ahead now, eight miles.

613
01:30:00,940 --> 01:30:05,320
Wood, you got them? They must
be close. I'm getting a hard-on.

614
01:30:12,660 --> 01:30:19,790
- I'm taking the lead. Let's identify them.
- Roger. I'm on your leftside, a little low.

615
01:30:20,040 --> 01:30:22,920
Maverick's up and ready in alert five.

616
01:30:25,800 --> 01:30:30,220
Mybogey's still locked up.
