646
01:33:50,850 --> 01:33:53,650
Get control!

647
01:34:00,200 --> 01:34:05,790
- Good recovery.
- Let's get in there and help lce.

648
01:34:06,040 --> 01:34:10,790
- Let's get back in the game.
- No, it's no good.

649
01:34:13,840 --> 01:34:18,920
- Goddamn it. Maverick's disengaging.
- I knew it. Shit!

650
01:34:22,180 --> 01:34:27,640
Get in there, come on.
What the hell are you doing?

651
01:34:27,890 --> 01:34:33,730
- Ice won't last down there alone ...
- Talk to me, Goose.

652
01:34:33,980 --> 01:34:37,530
Maverick!

653
01:34:39,530 --> 01:34:42,110
Maverick's re-engaging, sir.

654
01:34:46,990 --> 01:34:51,500
- I can't get him off my tail.
- I've got your MiG dead ahead.

655
01:34:53,080 --> 01:34:56,790
I got tone. Firing!

656
01:35:07,400 --> 01:35:10,650
- Where are they?.
- 155 miles.

657
01:35:10,900 --> 01:35:16,230
- Two MiGs dead ahead.
- I see them. I'll take it left.

658
01:35:18,160 --> 01:35:21,790
Oh, my God.

659
01:35:22,030 --> 01:35:26,750
Ice is right below with a MiG on his tail.

660
01:35:27,000 --> 01:35:29,670
He's firing. Break left!

661
01:35:31,960 --> 01:35:34,840
He overshot!

662
01:35:35,090 --> 01:35:40,520
Coming in, lce.
I got two MiGs, dead ahead.

663
01:35:42,390 --> 01:35:45,100
One MiG passing between us.

664
01:35:48,440 --> 01:35:52,240
You've got a MiG on your left.
He's gonna fire!

665
01:36:00,240 --> 01:36:03,290
Check the guy to the north!

666
01:36:05,670 --> 01:36:08,790
Banking left.

667
01:36:10,130 --> 01:36:15,630
- There he is. Get him, lce!
- Okay, you guys, I'm coming in.

668
01:36:19,050 --> 01:36:23,140
- A MiG's coming round on our tail.
- I can't leave lce.

669
01:36:23,390 --> 01:36:28,150
- He's gonna get behind us!
- I'm not leaving my wingman.

670
01:36:31,020 --> 01:36:35,950
I'm on his tail. I'm going
for the shot right now. Roger, engaged!

671
01:36:39,070 --> 01:36:43,450
- I've got radar lock.
- I'm taking the shot. Fire!

672
01:36:48,340 --> 01:36:51,850
- Bingo!
- Watch out, there's a MiG to your right.

673
01:36:52,100 --> 01:36:54,850
He's firing!

674
01:36:55,100 --> 01:37:01,310
- I'm hit. We're hit in the right engine.
- I'm shutting it down.

675
01:37:06,280 --> 01:37:09,700
Coming in, lce.

676
01:37:11,740 --> 01:37:16,410
That bogey's still behind you.
I'm manoeuvring for a shot.

677
01:37:16,660 --> 01:37:19,670
- Take the shot.
- I can't get a tone.

678
01:37:19,920 --> 01:37:23,170
Shoot. I can't get him off my tail.

679
01:37:26,670 --> 01:37:30,090
- We're hit again.
- We're okay.

680
01:37:30,340 --> 01:37:33,140
On the count of three, break hard right.

681
01:37:33,390 --> 01:37:37,020
Three ... two ... one ... break right!

682
01:37:40,230 --> 01:37:43,480
Firing!

683
01:37:45,780 --> 01:37:49,320
- Damn it, I missed.
- Don't let him go.

684
01:37:49,570 --> 01:37:53,570
I got him. Here comes the shot.

685
01:37:59,710 --> 01:38:02,750
Strike three.

686
01:38:03,000 --> 01:38:07,760
- There's a MiG on your tail.
- We've only got one missile left.

687
01:38:08,010 --> 01:38:10,800
1 10 miles, sir.

688
01:38:11,050 --> 01:38:13,760
I got him. He's on our tail.

689
01:38:20,730 --> 01:38:25,020
He's still with us.

690
01:38:27,480 --> 01:38:32,360
- You're slowing down.
- I'm bringing him in closer.

691
01:38:37,750 --> 01:38:42,250
- This is it.
- I'll hit the brakes. He'll fly right by us.

692
01:38:46,220 --> 01:38:48,510
Now!

693
01:38:52,510 --> 01:38:55,050
I've got a good lock. Firing.

694
01:38:58,780 --> 01:39:01,100
Strike four!

695
01:39:04,820 --> 01:39:10,450
This is Voodoo Three.
Remaining MiGs are bugging out.

696
01:39:23,550 --> 01:39:29,140
- This is Maverick, requesting fly-by.
- Negative, the pattern is full.

697
01:39:31,850 --> 01:39:34,730
Is there something I should know about?

698
01:39:53,290 --> 01:39:55,960
Goddamn that guy.

699
01:40:51,100 --> 01:40:55,030
You!

700
01:40:55,280 --> 01:40:59,240
You are still dangerous.

701
01:41:01,700 --> 01:41:05,040
But you can be my wingman anytime.

702
01:41:05,290 --> 01:41:09,790
Bullshit. You can be mine.

703
01:42:00,220 --> 01:42:05,300
Maverick?. You're on the front pages
of all the English-speaking world.

704
01:42:05,560 --> 01:42:09,480
Even though the other side
denies the incident, congratulations.

705
01:42:09,730 --> 01:42:16,150
They gave you your choice of duty, son.
Where do you think you want to go?

706
01:42:16,400 --> 01:42:20,960
- I thought of being an instructor, sir.
- Top Gun?

707
01:42:21,210 --> 01:42:24,740
- Yes, sir.
- God help us.

708
01:43:45,410 --> 01:43:48,380
Hello, Pete Mitchell.

709
01:43:51,420 --> 01:43:57,050
I heard the best of the best
were gonna be back here, so ...

710
01:44:01,060 --> 01:44:04,430
This could be complicated.

711
01:44:04,690 --> 01:44:08,650
You know,
on the first one, I crashed and burned.

712
01:44:08,900 --> 01:44:13,230
And the second?

713
01:44:18,910 --> 01:44:21,250
I don't know.

714
01:44:21,260 --> 01:44:25,550
But it's looking good so far.

